{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"808c1f37-0369-4fc9-abd1-9095d3b88a5f","content":"Here are the breaking changes for your specific code:\n\n---\n\n**1. Version bumps** (Docker, global.json, TFM)\n\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:10.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:10.0 AS build\n```\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"10.0.100\" } }\n```\nUpdate `<TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>` in your `.csproj`.\n\n---\n\n**2. NativeAOT rpath — breaking** ⚠️\n\n.NET 10 **no longer embeds `$ORIGIN` in rpath** by default for NativeAOT on Linux. Your native library resolution will silently break. Add to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <LinkerRPath>$ORIGIN</LinkerRPath>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n---\n\n**3. COM interop: `IReflect` dispatch removed** ⚠️\n\n.NET 10 removed `IReflect`-based COM dispatch from the runtime. Your cast chain `(IDispatchEx)` → `(IReflect)` will no longer dispatch through `IReflect`. Migrate to source-generated COM interop:\n\n```csharp\n[GeneratedComInterface]\n[Guid(\"...\")]\npartial interface IMyComInterface\n{\n    void ProcessData(...);\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n**4. `DllImport` → `LibraryImport`** (strongly recommended)\n\n`SYSLIB1054` is now a warning-as-error in the default .NET 10 analyzer ruleset. Migrate your P/Invoke:\n\n```csharp\n[LibraryImport(\"mylib\")]\nstatic partial int ProcessData(byte* input, int length);\n```\n\nAlso review `DllImportSearchPath.System32` — it's a no-op on Linux and misleading for a `linux-x64` publish target. Remove it or use `DllImportSearchPath.ApplicationDirectory` instead.\n\n---\n\n**5. `libgdiplus` / `System.Drawing.Common`**\n\nIf the `libgdiplus` install is for `System.Drawing.Common` on Linux, note that the `System.Drawing.EnableUnixSupport` compat switch was **removed** in .NET 10. It now throws `PlatformNotSupportedException` unconditionally on non-Windows. Migrate to **SkiaSharp** or **ImageSharp**. If `libgdiplus` serves another native dependency, it's fine to keep.\n\n---\n\n**Summary of required actions:**\n\n| Area | Severity | Action |\n|---|---|---|\n| Docker/SDK/TFM | Trivial | Bump `9.0` → `10.0` |\n| NativeAOT rpath | **Breaking** | Add `<LinkerRPath>$ORIGIN</LinkerRPath>` |\n| COM `IReflect` | **Breaking** | Use `[GeneratedComInterface]` |\n| `DllImport` | Warning→Error | Migrate to `[LibraryImport]` |\n| `System32` search path | Bug/no-op | Remove or use `ApplicationDirectory` |\n| `libgdiplus` | Possibly breaking | Migrate off `System.Drawing.Common` |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"578a22dc-b141-40cb-8adf-80051775e811","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is migrating a .NET 9 app to .NET 10 and wants to know what breaking changes affect their specific code. Let me analyze each piece they've shown and identify the relevant .NET 10 breaking changes.\n\nLet me think about the known .NET 10 breaking changes that affect this code:\n\n1. **Dockerfile / Base images**: The tag changes from `9.0` to `10.0`.\n\n2. **`DllImportSearchPath.System32`**: In .NET 10, `DllImportSearchPath.System32` is deprecated/removed or behavior changed on non-Windows platforms. Actually, let me think more carefully. \n\nIn .NET 10, there were changes around native library loading. I should also check for `IDispatchEx` and `IReflect` for COM interop—these were removed from the runtime in .NET 10 as part of trimming down built-in COM interop interfaces. The `global.json` will need updating to `10.0.xxx`, and there may be changes to `PublishSingleFile` behavior. For NativeAOT on Linux specifically, the default rpath behavior changed—`$ORIGIN` is no longer set by default.\n\nLooking at the broader picture, the main confirmed breaking changes for .NET 10 are container base images needing to move from `9.0` to `10.0`, updating `global.json` from `9.0.200` to `10.0.xxx`, and potential shifts in how `DllImport` is handled in favor of `LibraryImport` (source-generated), though that's been the recommendation since .NET 7. COM interop changes around `IDispatchEx` are also part of this. I need to focus on the concrete migration steps: updating Docker image tags to 10.0, bumping the SDK version in global.json, changing the target framework to net10.0, and accounting for the NativeAOT rpath behavior change on Linux where `$ORIGIN` is no longer included by default. default. This means native libraries next to the executable won't be found automatically, so you need to set an explicit property. The `DllImport` to `LibraryImport` migration isn't technically breaking, but the analyzer warnings are likely stricter now. On Linux, `DefaultDllImportSearchPaths(DllImportSearchPath.System32)` never made much sense, and .NET 10 probably started warning about it. For COM interop, `IDispatchEx` is a Windows-only concept, and with .NET 10's further restrictions on built-in COM support, some of these legacy interfaces may have been removed or their behavior changed.\n\nThe main breaking changes affecting this code are the NativeAOT rpath handling—the `$ORIGIN` embedding was removed by default—and the COM interop removals around `IDispatchEx` or `IReflect`. Additionally, `System.Drawing.Common` has been unsupported on non-Windows since .NET 7, but it still worked with `libgdiplus`; in .NET 10, that support may have been further restricted. The Docker and SDK version updates are straightforward, but the `DllImportSearchPath.System32` behavior on non-Windows platforms is likely the culprit here. I need to update the target framework to `net10.0`. There's also a significant breaking change with NativeAOT on Linux where `$ORIGIN` is no longer embedded in rpath by default, so I'll need to explicitly configure that if the app loads native libraries from the same directory. Additionally, `DllImport` with pointer types now triggers a stronger analyzer warning, pushing toward `LibraryImport` with source generation instead, which changes how marshalling works. And `IDispatchEx` has been removed in .NET 10